description: Sum of 13 but no fewer nonzero fourth powers.
links: Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, Biquadratic Number.
mathematica: isSumQ[n_] := Do[pr = PowersRepresentations[n, k, 4]; If[k < 13, If[pr != {} , Return[False]], If[k == 13 && pr != {}, Return[True], Return[False]]], {k, 1, 13}]; Reap[For[n = 1, n <= 800, n++, If[isSumQ[n], Print[n]; Sow[n]]]][[2, 1]] (* _Jean-FranÃ§ois Alcover_, Oct 25 2012 *)
author: _Eric W. Weisstein_
